      "side": 1,
      "message": "sure, all core server shit should be on the main handler. But the main handler won\u0027t be reached if someone happened to call VirtualHost(\"main host\"), right? For example, today ResultDB has one virtual host today, for user content. We decided its OK not to do VirtualHost for pRPC handlers because we know they never serve HTML. But, if we add some HTML handlers there, we don\u0027t want them to accidentally go on the userContentHost. I was under impression that on that case, we\u0027d want to host UI on explicit VirtualHost(\u003cmain host\u003e), which would break this thing. Did I misunderstood your earlier recommendation?\n\nIf clients should never call VirtualHost(\u003cmain host\u003e), then please add a comment to VirtualHost func. Separate CL is fine.",
      "parentUuid": "6745cd29_7f12e430",
      "revId": "e4ac0c3f9a5a3369d36f742f5f1d4073511442dd",
